On Mon, 29 Jun 2009, Darren Evans-Young wrote:

> ...I adjust the cable again...even more spacers, but
> pedal still goes to the floor and wont disengage the clutch. When a
> helper presses the pedal, the clutch lever does not move as much as
> I expect it should.
>
> I wonder if my bowden tube does not have enough bend in it. Any ideas?
> Is this a more serious clutch issue, requiring and engine drop?

It sounds like the throwout fork inside the bell housing is broken. 
That's a pull-the-engine job.

The only other possibility is that the lever arm at the front is broken or 
slipping in some way.  I doubt it though if you're getting movement at the 
transmission end of the cable.
